author: SportsDayDFW.com
title: Charlie Strong squashes Miami rumors: Texas is 'best job in the country'
text:
First question to Charlie Strong: "You going to Miami?" Says Strong: "I have the best job in the country."
— Chuck Carlton (@ChuckCarltonDMN) October 26, 2015
Strong says he hasn't lost faith in Heard's passing ability.
— Nick Castillo (@Nick_Castillo74) October 26, 2015
Strong says D'Onta Foreman is in a boot for precautionary reasons. He expects him to play against Iowa State.
— Nick Castillo (@Nick_Castillo74) October 26, 2015
"He's such a solid person," - Strong on Tyrone Swoopes' character after losing starting job.
— Nick Castillo (@Nick_Castillo74) October 26, 2015
"That's all we got so let's go play with them," Strong on seeing so many young players on the field.
— Nick Castillo (@Nick_Castillo74) October 26, 2015 On Twitter:
 @SportsDayDFW
